    "title": "Cats & Histograms",
    "long_instructions": "####Cats and Histograms\r\nThis data is about 24 domesticated cats. Explore the data and answer the data questions:\r\n- Are older cats predominantly male or female?\r\n- What is the typical body length of a domesticated cat?\r\n\r\n[Google Sheets Link](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1ANuZhH77nTzvx6DI5Pq5OnmVAno2dqef4OsihHwHD38/edit?gid=0#gid=0)\r\n\r\n**Do This**\r\n1. Add graphs to the workspace and the appropriate attributes you think might be helpful to answer the data question, “Are older cats predominantly male or female?”\r\n\r\n    :::details [**Show Me How**]\r\n    - Sort the data by the \"Sex\" column\r\n    - Make a histogram of the \"Age\" values for female\r\n    - Make a histogram of the \"Age\" values for male\r\n    - What do you notice?\r\n    - Are older cats predominantly male or female? How can you tell?\r\n    :::\r\n\r\n2. Add a new graph to the workspace and the appropriate attributes that you think might be helpful to answer the data question, “What is the typical body length of a domesticated cat?”\r\n\r\n    :::details [**Show Me How**]\r\n    - Make a histogram of the \"BodyLength\" values\r\n    - What do you notice?\r\n    - What is the typical body length of a domesticated cat? How can you tell?\r\n    :::\r\n\r\n",
